Long format
===========

GNATkp: the GNAT known problem detector

Usage: gnatkp --RTS=<runtime> [-P<proj>] [name] [opts]

 name is zero or more file names (wildcards allowed)

general options:

 -log           duplicate all messages sent to stderr in gnatkp.log
 -V, --version  show the tool version and exit
 -h, --help     show the help message and exit

gnatkp help:

 --list-rules              show the list of predefined rules and exit
 --check-semantic          check semantic validity of the source files
 --no-subprojects          process only sources of root project
 -U
           process all units of the closure rooted in the mains passed as
           arguments (or mains of the project if list is empty)
 --charset <charset>
           specify the charset of the source files (default is latin-1)
 --kp-version <version>    enable all KP detectors matching GNAT <version>
 -l                        full pathname for file locations
 -q                        quiet mode, do not emit messages on stderr
 -v, --verbose             enable the verbose mode
 --brief
           report rule violation detections on stderr, suppress other messages
           (implies -s)
 -s                        print the short version of the report file
 -o <file>                 specify the name of the text report file
 --sarif <file>            specify the name of the SARIF report file
 --show-instantiation-chain
           show instantiation chain for reported generic construct
 -j <n>                    the maximal number of processes
 -r, --rule <rule>         enable the given rules for the run
 --rule-file <file>        read rule configuration from the given LKQL rule file
 -W, --warnings-as-errors  treat warning messages as errors
 -rules <opts>             deprecated rule options

GPR specific options:

 --ignore-project-switches  ignore switches specified in the project file
 -vP <level>
           set the verbosity level for project file parsing (0: quiet, 1:
           warnings, 2: verbose; default: 0)
 -aP <Search path>          Add directory to the project search path
 --autoconf <autoconf> [<autoconf>...]
           Specify/create the main config project file name
 --config <config>          Specify the configuration project file name
 --db <db>                  Parse dir as an additional knowledge base
 --db-                      Do not load the standard knowledge base
 --implicit-with <project>
           Add the given projects as a dependency on all loaded projects
 -eL                        Follows symlinks for project files
 --no-project               Do not use a project file
 -P <project>               The project file
 --print-gpr-registry       Print the GPR registry
 --root-dir <root-dir>      Root directory of obj/lib/exec to relocate
 --relocate-build-tree <relocate-build-tree>
           Root obj/lib/exec dirs are current-directory or dir
 --RTS <rts>                Use --RTS=<runtime> to specify the Ada runtime
 --RTS <rts-index>
           Use --RTS:<lang>=<runtime> to specify the runtime for language <lang>
 --src-subdirs <src-subdirs>
           prepend <obj>/dir to the list of source dirs for each project
 --subdirs <subdirs>        Use dir as suffix to obj/lib/exec directories
 --target <target>          Specify a target <target> cross platforms
 -X <scenario>              Specify an external reference for Project Files


Report bugs to support@adacore.com

